  "break-even": "Deterministic browser-local break-even methodology available in English, French, Swahili and Hausa. Contribution per unit equals selling price minus variable cost per unit. Contribution ratio equals contribution per unit divided by selling price. Exact break-even units equal fixed costs divided by contribution per unit. Whole break-even units round the exact units up. Exact threshold revenue equals fixed costs divided by contribution ratio; revenue at whole units equals whole units times selling price and can be slightly higher. Planned profit or loss and margin of safety remain signed. Fixed costs may be zero. Planned units and target profit are optional, but any supplied value must be finite and non-negative. Selling price must be positive and greater than variable cost. The optional unit is display-only. Never supply or infer VAT, tax, duty, exchange rates, market prices, industry benchmarks, demand forecasts, pricing recommendations or funding claims. Inputs and exports remain in the browser.",
  "brideprice-advisor": "African bride price and marriage traditions expert. You provide culturally sensitive guidance on bridewealth customs across 20+ ethnic groups. Key traditions: Igba Nkwu (Igbo, Nigeria) — palm wine, kola nut, cash, traditional items, typically ₦500K-₦5M total. Eru Iyawo (Yoruba) — engagement list including Bible/Quran, honey, salt, sugar, clothing, typically ₦300K-₦2M. Lobola (Zulu, Xhosa, Tswana) — 8-12 cattle or R50K-R200K cash equivalent. Maasai (Kenya/Tanzania) — cattle, typically 5-15 cows. Dowry vs bride price: most African cultures practice bride price (groom's family pays), NOT dowry. Modern trends: negotiation is becoming more flexible, cash increasingly accepted alongside traditional items. Cultural do's: show respect to elders, bring a spokesperson, dress appropriately. Don'ts: never negotiate directly, don't haggle aggressively, don't rush the process.",
  "burial-cost": "Estimate funeral and burial costs in Nigeria, Kenya, Ghana, South Africa. Local packages.",
  "business-name-gen": "Deterministic browser-local business-name shortlist workshop in English, French and Swahili. It combines up to five user-supplied keywords, an optional user-supplied local word, selected industry, audience, tone, pattern and length target through fixed reusable patterns. The transparent readability heuristic checks only length target, one-or-two-word form, keyword connection, triple repeated characters and simple characters. It is not a measure of commercial quality, uniqueness, registrability or legal safety. AfroTools supplies no translation, linguistic meaning, company-name availability, trademark clearance, domain availability, social-handle availability or official registry result. The working shortlist is session-only, is not persisted or sent to a server, and can be copied or exported locally as CSV, JSON, PDF or print. The AI manifest is route-only and accepts no name brief or prefill data.",
  "business-plan-builder": "Deterministic browser-local SME Business Plan Draft Workshop in English, French and Swahili. It structures only user-entered business evidence, operations, risks, milestones and financial assumptions. Gross contribution is monthly revenue minus monthly variable costs. Operating profit is contribution minus monthly fixed operating costs. Funding gap is the positive difference between startup plus working-capital need and confirmed funding. Same-mix break-even revenue is fixed costs divided by a positive contribution ratio. Simple undiscounted payback divides startup plus working-capital need by positive monthly operating profit and is explicitly not break-even. Low and high scenarios apply a user-entered revenue change while holding the base variable-cost ratio and fixed costs constant. Currency is a display label only. No tax, interest rate, funding term, programme eligibility, market data, approval probability, lender-ready status or official application is supplied. Business narrative and finances remain session-only unless the user explicitly saves a versioned draft in local browser storage. Local copy, TXT, formula-safe CSV, JSON, parser-readable PDF and print exports are available. The AI manifest is route-only and accepts no business content or financial prefill.",
