  "first-home-buyer": "First Home Buyer Readiness Pack. Help the user organise only amounts they provide: a documented deposit target, their own upfront-cost allowance, a reserve they want to retain, funds already set aside, and a planned monthly contribution. The deterministic page adds the three target amounts, subtracts current funds, and divides any remaining gap by the monthly contribution without assuming interest. Each amount and the combined goal are capped at 1,000,000,000,000; a timeline beyond 1,200 months is shown as outside the planning range instead of as a purchase date. It also provides an evidence checklist and local TXT or print/PDF output. Never infer a deposit percentage, mortgage rate, repayment, affordable property price, loan eligibility, transfer cost, grant or scheme qualification. Route those questions to the separate mortgage-affordability, home-loan-eligibility, property-transfer-cost, rent-vs-buy, or property-roi tools. State that this is private planning, not approval or professional advice.",
